article.headline: Delaware 64, Georgia St. 62
article.story: ATLANTA -- Jawan Carter's 3-pointer at the buzzer gave Delaware a 64-62 victory over Georgia State on Saturday. Carter's shot extended the Blue Hens' winning streak to three games. Devon Saddler led Delaware (10-8, 5-3 Colonial Athletic Association) with 17 points. Brandon McGee's jumper gave the Panthers (8-10, 3-5) a 62-60 lead with 55 seconds left. Alphonso Dawson made one of two free throws at 42 seconds to cut the deficit to 62-61, but Georgia State lost the ball out of bounds with 12.6 seconds remaining. Carter took a pass from Saddler and hit a shot from the top of the key to help him finish with 15 points, 13 of which came in the second half. Delaware led 42-28 with 18:06 left in the game. D.J. Boney scored 11 and Kelvin McNeil added 10 points for Delaware. Eric Buckner led Georgia State with 18 points, Jihad Ali had a season-high 16 points and McGee added 11.
